{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01VUbupnZ9FEwGvu3ocrGb38","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deployment is complete and verified.\n\n## Summary\n\nA 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster is deployed in the `elasticsearch` namespace using only native Kubernetes resources (no CRDs/operators).\n\n**Resources created** (`es.yaml`):\n- **StatefulSet `es`** — 3 replicas (es-0/1/2), all `1/1 Ready`, image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`, each with a 2Gi PVC.\n- **Service `es-http`** (ClusterIP) — HTTPS on port 9200, the entrypoint for clients.\n- **Service `es-discovery`** (headless) — transport/9300 for node discovery.\n- **ConfigMap `es-config`** — `elasticsearch.yml` with security + HTTP TLS (from `es-http-tls`) + transport TLS enabled.\n- **PodDisruptionBudget `es-pdb`** — `minAvailable: 2`.\n- Used the existing `elastic-password` secret to set the `elastic` user password.\n\n**Verification:**\n- Cluster health via `https://es-http:9200`: **green, 3 nodes, 3 data nodes**.\n- **Write**: indexed a doc → `\"result\":\"created\"`.\n- **Read**: GET returned the doc; search matched it.\n- **Replica allocation**: a 1-replica index reached `green` (primary + replica on separate nodes), confirming genuine multi-node operation.\n\n**Key gotcha hit and fixed:** the initial StatefulSet used the default `OrderedReady` pod management, which deadlocked — es-0 couldn't pass its readiness probe (needs cluster quorum) so es-1/es-2 never started. Recreating the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` let all three boot together, form quorum, and elect a master.\n\nGoal met: all nodes Ready, reachable over HTTPS through `es-http`, reads and writes succeed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1088,"cache_read_input_tokens":67123,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1088},